import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='value', by='budgetYear', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Budget Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Value')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='forecastYear')
    plt.plot(data['forecastYear'], data['value'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of values over forecast years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['value'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between budget year and value?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['forecastYear'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['value'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='value')
    ax.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median value')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of values across forecast years?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('budgetYear').mean()
    plt.bar(data.index, data['value'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['value'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average value')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budget year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
